				\begin{document}$$ Z\left(\omega \right)=\frac{R_1}{1+ j\omega {R}_1{C}_1}. $$\end{document}

After the approximation of the impedance spectra of the PS structure, the following values were derived: R1 = 10.3 MΩ and C1 = 177 pF. In the second model for the PS, the resistive–capacitive properties of the system are described using the constant phase element (CPE) in the equivalent circuit as shown in inset Fig. 7b. Expression for the impedance of the R–CPE model will be the following [38]:Zω=R21+jωnR2Q,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
