				\begin{document}$$ Z\left(\omega \right)=\frac{R_2}{1+{\left( j\omega \right)}^n{R}_2 Q}, $$\end{document}

According to the model for the PS–RGO structure, the total impedance Z(ω) of the sample can be represented by two RC (parallel resistor and capacitor) sub-circuits connected in series. Moreover, low-frequency RBCB and high-frequency RVCV sub-circuits correspond to the process of transfer of charge carriers through the boundary and in the bulk of silicon nanocrystals, respectively. For the analysis of this model, it is also appropriate to use the CPE. After replacing the CB capacitor by CPE, the expression for the impedance of the PS–RGO structures will be the following:Zω=R0+RV1+jωRVCV+RB1+jωnRBQ.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
